    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's the complete implementation plan for the model rename feature across **4 files** in **7 steps**:\n\n---\n\n### `api/types.go` — Step 1\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct after `CopyRequest` (line ~765):\n```go\ntype RenameRequest struct {\n    Source      string `json:\"source\"`\n    Destination string `json:\"destination\"`\n}\n```\n\n### `api/client.go` — Step 2\nAdd `Rename()` method after `Copy()` (line ~387):\n```go\nfunc (c *Client) Rename(ctx context.Context, req *RenameRequest) error {\n    if err := c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil); err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### `server/routes.go` — Steps 3 & 4\nAdd `RenameHandler` method after `CopyHandler` (~line 1483) implementing:\n- JSON body parsing (same as `CopyHandler`)\n- Empty-field validation → 400\n- `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n- Destination-exists check via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → 409 Conflict\n- `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 on `os.ErrNotExist`\n- Source deletion via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()`\n- 200 `{\"status\": \"success\"}` on success\n\nThen register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` immediately after `/api/copy` (~line 1698).\n\n**No new imports needed** — `errtypes`, `model`, `manifest`, `errors`, `fmt`, `io`, `os` are all already imported.\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` — Steps 5, 6, & 7\n- Add `RenameHandler` func after `CopyHandler` (~line 1350): creates client, calls `client.Rename()`, prints `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"`\n- Add `renameCmd` cobra.Command after `copyCmd` (~line 2265): `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`\n- Register `renameCmd` between `copyCmd` and `deleteCmd` in `rootCmd.AddCommand()`",
